reviews.text:
I was craving for banana pie and chanced upon Han’s so I decided to give their version a try. Plus, this newly renovated branch looks so inviting.

Unfortunately, the $4.20 pie was served cold and fell short of expectations. The crust was dry, and the banana filling could be more aromatic.

Surprisingly, my accompanying Kopi C was actually better than expected. I may return to try other cooked dishes next time.

Just want to ask?
Is your chicken pie suppose to be ice cold ?
I brought a chicken pie at 930am
Brought it home took a bite inside is Ice cold?

Worst place to have breakfast.
Please if you can't wake up don't come to work , if u want to be lazy then before u sell ur cold food remember to microwave first

Give a 5 stars for the atmosphere as it’s not crowded and the tables are clean.
Ordered a set of fish & chips, a set of Grilled fish, seafood HorFan & Omelette with cheese and mushrooms.
Fish & Chips / Grilled fish - worth eating because it’s come with Soup of the day and ice lemon tea.
Seafood horfan - not bad can eat
Omelette -  food for children
Service staffs at the cashier are friendly.

Ordered fish & chips. Fries not bad.  Fish totally cannot make it.  Whole thing is like hollow & the fish meat super pathetic.   The amount of flour is so wow wow.  Wat de fish…

Upstairs Long John silver can easily win 2 streets..
You need to do something about your service. Your outlet is clearly under-staffed with one person doing order-taking plus preparing drinks. No wonder the queue is so long.
